Sec. 165.022. METHOD OF DISEASE ERADICATION. (a) Following
notice and public hearing, the commission shall adopt rules for the
enforcement of this subchapter, including rules providing for the
manner, method, and system of eradicating swine diseases.
(b) The commission may by a two-thirds vote adopt rules under
this section that are more stringent than the minimum standards for
cooperative programs adopted by the Animal and Plant Health
Inspection Service of the United States Department of Agriculture.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1429, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by:
Acts 2021, 87th Leg., R.S., Ch. 623 (S.B. 1997), Sec. 4, eff.
September 1, 2021.

